ed in the [[Khalsi]] [[tehsil]].\n\n== Demographics ==\n\nAccording to the [[2011 census of India]], Tia has 196 households. The effective literacy rate (i.e. the literacy rate of population excluding children aged 6 and below) is 70.2%.<ref name=\"census_2011\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Demographics (2011 Census)<ref name=\"census_2011\">{{cite news |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/datagov/CDB_PCA_Census/PCA_CDB_0103_F_Census.xls |title=Leh district census |work=[[2011 Census of India]] |publisher=Directorate of Census Operations |accessdate=2015-07-23 }}</ref>\n! !! Total !! Male !! Female\n|-\n| Population || 1273 || 591 || 682\n|-\n| Children aged below 6 years || 132 || 68 || 64\n|-\n| [[Scheduled caste]] || 1 || 1 || 0\n|-\n| [[Scheduled tribe]] || 1261 || 587 || 674\n|-\n| Literates || 801 || 395 || 406\n|-\n| Workers (all) || 416 || 271 || 145\n|-\n| Main workers (total) || 374 || 244 || 130\n|-\n| Main workers: Cultivators || 149 || 80 || 69\n|-\n| Main workers: Agricultural labourers || 0 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| Main workers: Household industry workers || 5 || 5 || 0\n|-\n| Main workers: Other || 220 || 159 || 61\n|-\n| Marginal workers (total) || 42 || 27 || 15\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Cultivators || 22 || 16 || 6\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Agricultural labourers || 4 || 2 || 2\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Household industry workers || 2 || 1 || 1\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Others || 14 || 8 || 6\n|-\n| Non-workers || 857 || 320 || 537\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Leh district}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Khalsi tehsil]]\n", "name_user": "FlyJet777", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor edits", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tia,_Leh"}
{"title_page": "Just the Way You Are (Bruno Mars song)", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Just the Way You Are\n| cover      = Bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Bruno Mars]]\n| album      = [[Doo-Wops & Hooligans]]\n| released   = July 20, 2010\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Pop music|Pop]]|[[soft rock]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length     = 3:41\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Elektra Records|Elektra]]|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|Bruno Mars|[[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]]|Ari Levine|[[Saint Cassius (musician)|Khalil Walton]]|[[Needlz|Khari Cain]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[The Smeezingtons]]|[[Needlz]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Billionaire (song)|Billionaire]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Grenade (song)|Grenade]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\n\"'''Just the Way You Are'''\" is the debut solo single by American singer-songwriter [[Bruno Mars]]. It is the lead single from his debut studio album, ''[[Doo-Wops & Hooligans]]'' (2010). The song was written by Bruno Mars, [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]], Ari Levine, [[Saint Cassius (musician)|Khalil Walton]] and [[Needlz]] and produced by the former three, under their alias, [[The Smeezingtons]] along with Needlz. It was released in the United States to [[Contemporary hit radio]] on August 10, 2010. The track was released in the United Kingdom on September 19, 2010, as \"'''Just the Way You Are (Amazing)'''\". The song's lyrics compliment a woman's beauty.\n\nThe debut single received mixed reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]], who praised The Smeezingtons\u2019 production, but dubbed its lyrics as sappy and corny. It won a [[Grammy Award for Best Male Pop Vocal Performance]] at the [[2011 Grammy Awards|2011 ceremony]]. The song peaked at number one on the [[Billboard Hot 100|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100]], Australia, Canada, New Zealand and in the United Kingdom charts and peaked in the top five in other countries. It was certified diamond by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA), seven and six times platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) and [[Music Canada]] (MC), respectively. \"Just the Way You Are\" was the best selling digital single of 2011, selling more than 12.5 million copies, thus joining an elite group of [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles worldwide]].\n\nThe music video, directed by Ethan Lader, was released on September 8, 2010 and features [[Peruvians|Peruvian]] born [[Australians|Australian]] actress [[Nathalie Kelley]]. The official remix features rapper [[Lupe Fiasco]] and is included on the deluxe edition of ''Doo-Wops & Hooligans'' (2010). Mars performed \"Just The Way You Are\" on [[The Doo-Wops & Hooligans Tour]] (2010\u20132012), on the [[Moonshine Jungle Tour]] (2013\u20132014) and on the [[24K Magic World Tour]] (2017-2018). He also included it during his performance at the [[Super Bowl XLVIII halftime show]]. \"Just the Way You Are\" has been covered by various recording artists and it inspired [[Meghan Trainor]]'s debut single \"[[All About That Bass]]\".<ref name=\"Sullivan\">{{cite news|author=Sullivan, Caroline|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2014/sep/01/pops-weighty-issue-all-about-that-bass-body-positive-anthems|title=Pop's weighty issue: All About That Bass and other body-positive anthems|work=The Guardian|date=September 1, 2014|accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Writing and production==\nMars said of the song, \"It took me months to come up with 'Just the Way You Are'... I wasn't thinking of anything deep or poetic. I was telling a story. Get ready to fall in love!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.4music.com/news/interviews/137/4Music.com-meets-Bruno-Mars|title=4Music.com meets Bruno Mars|publisher=[[4Music]]|date=September 22, 2010|accessdate=October 24, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810102419/http://www.4music.com/news/interviews/137/4Music.com-meets-Bruno-Mars|archivedate=August 10, 2011}}</ref> He added, \"I'm a big fan of songs like [[Joe Cocker]]'s '[[You Are So Beautiful]]' and [[Eric Clapton]]'s '[[Wonderful Tonight]]' - songs that go straight to the point. You know, there's no mind-boggling lyrics or twists in the story - they just come directly from the heart. And to me 'Just The Way You Are' is one of those songs. There's nothing mind-blowing about it. I'm just telling a woman she looks beautiful the way she IS - and, let's be honest, what woman doesn't wanna hear those lyrics?!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bluesandsoul.com/feature/593/bruno_mars_out_of_this_world/|title=Bruno Mars interview by Pete Lewis, 'Blues & Soul' October 2010|issue=1079|work=[[Blues & Soul]]|date=October 2010|accessdate=October 24, 2010}}</ref> \nMars' [[Artists and repertoire|A&R]] was responsible for finding the original idea from producers/ songwriters Khalil Walton and Needlz. Mars originally sang the hook that Khalil and Needlz wrote for a feature on a [[Lupe Fiasco]] record. Needlz allowed Mars to use the idea for his album.<ref name=\"hitquarters.com\"/><ref name=\"Producing Bruno Mars\"/> This was all facilitated by Aaron Bay Shuck, who told [[HitQuarters]] that as soon as \"Just the Way You Are\" was finished they knew they had the first single, saying:\n<blockquote>\"It had a massive chorus, an instantly memorable melody and lyric, and was a natural transition from the [[B.o.B]] and [[Travie McCoy]] songs ... [Also] it didn\u2019t sound like anything else on the radio. It had everything we could want in a first single for Bruno.\"<ref name=\"hitquarters.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_AaronBaySchuck_int.html|title=Interview with Aaron Bay-Schuck|publisher=[[HitQuarters]]|date=December 13, 2010|accessdate=December 14, 2010|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120524145029/http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_AaronBaySchuck_int.html|archivedate=May 24, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nAri Levine explains: \"Needlz had a track with a melody idea by Khalil Walton that was presented to us by one of the A&R guys. Bruno and Phil came up with the chorus, and then Needlz sent us the files and we replaced a bunch of sounds with our sounds and I programmed drums in the [[Music Production Center|MPC]], and we wrote the rest of the song. I never met Needlz or Walton\".<ref name=\"Producing Bruno Mars\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/jun11/articles/smeezingtons.htm|title=Ari Levine & The Smeezingtons: Producing Bruno Mars|work=[[Sound on Sound]]|first=Paul|last=Tingen|date=June 2011|accessdate=July 27, 2013}}</ref>\nThe song was supposed to be for [[Lupe Fiasco]] but at this point, Bruno decided to keep it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KhcmjSbSyPg|title=ASCAP Grammy Brunch - Bruno Mars Producer Needlz Interview|author=PacificRimVideoPress|publisher=[[Youtube.com]]|date=February 12, 2012|accessdate=September 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\n\"Just the Way You Are\" was co-written by Mars, [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]], Ari Levine, [[Saint Cassius (musician)|Khalil Walton]] and [[Needlz]], while production was handled by the former three production-team, [[The Smeezingtons]]. Levine, Needlz, and Mars played all the instruments on the track and recorded them. Ari was also responsible for engineering the song at Levcon Studios in California. The track was mixed at Larrabee Sound Studios in Los Angeles by [[Manny Marroquin]], while Christian Plata and Erik Madrid served as mixing assistants. It was mastered by [[Stephen Marcussen]] at Marcussen Mastering in Hollywood, California.<ref name=\"Notes\">{{cite AV media notes |title= Doo-Wops & Hooligans |titlelink= Doo-Wops & Hooligans |year=2010 |type=CD booklet |publisher= [[Elektra Entertainment Group]] |id= 2-525393 |location= [[United States]]}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\"Just The Way You Are\" was released as the lead single from ''[[Doo-Wops & Hooligans]]''.<ref name=\"Marketwire\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/Bruno-Mars-Unveils-Eagerly-Awaited-Debut-Album-DOO-WOPS-HOOLIGANS-Slated-Arrive-October-1309664.htm|title=Bruno Mars Unveils Eagerly Awaited Debut Album \"Doo-Wops & Hooligans\" Slated to Arrive October 5th; New Single \"Just The Way You Are\" Shaping Up as Massive Hit, With Top 3 Success on iTunes \"Top Singles\"; Sold-Out New York City Live Debut Set for Tonight, Followed by US Tour Alongside Maroon 5 in October|date=August 25, 2010|publisher=Marketwire|accessdate=August 25, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101001094834/http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/Bruno-Mars-Unveils-Eagerly-Awaited-Debut-Album-DOO-WOPS-HOOLIGANS-Slated-Arrive-October-1309664.htm|archivedate=October 1, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Elektra Records]] serviced the song to download in the United States on July 20, 2010.<ref name=\"Marketwire\"/> It was released in the United States to [[Contemporary hit radio]] on August 10, 2010 by Elktra and Atlatic Records.<ref name=\"FMQB\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=69239#2010 |title=Radio Industry News, Music Industry Updates, Arbitron Ratings, Music News and more! |magazine=FMQB |accessdate=September 5, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130424132118/http://www.fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=69239 |archivedate=April 24, 2013 }}</ref> On September 19, 2010, the song was sent to the United Kingdom to be released, under the name, Just the Way You Are (Amazing), on Mainstream Radio.<ref name=\"4music\">{{cite web|url=http://www.4music.com/artists/38/Bruno-Mars|title=Introducing Bruno Mars|date=September 5, 2010|publisher=4Music|accessdate=September 22, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622093631/http://www.4music.com/artists/38/Bruno-Mars|archivedate=June 22, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"sc_UK_Bruno Mars\" /> On November 2, seven remixes were released as a purchasable download in US.<ref name=\"Remixes EP\"/> It was released as a CD single in Germany, Austria, and Switzerland, on November 12. The single contains the album version of the song and the remix by Skrillex Batboi.<ref name=\"CD singleGAS\">{{cite AV media notes|title=''\"Just the Way You Are\"''|others=Bruno Mars|year=2010|type=Liner notes/CD single|publisher=Elektra|id=7567-88334-96}}</ref> The track was released on September 27, 2010 in the United Kingdom via digital download.<ref name=\"Digital Spy Review\"/> On November 2, 2011, an EP that includes several remixes was released worldwide. Skrillex, Martin Danielle and the Manufactured Superstars were among the names to remix the original version into electronic dance music versions.<ref name=\"Remixes EP\"/> A deluxe edition which includes the official remix with rapper [[Lupe Fiasco]] and the music video was released on November 25, 2010, worldwide.<ref name=\"Deluxe single\"/> The official remix was also released on the deluxe edition of ''Doo-Wops & Hooligans'' (2010).<ref name=\"Soars\">{{Cite press release|url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/Bruno-Mars-Soars-1-on-Billboard-Hot-100-Chart-With-Debut-Single-Just-The-Way-You-Are-1323732.htm|title=Bruno Mars Soars to #1 on the Billboard Hot 100 Chart With Debut Single \"Just The Way You Are\"; Single Lands the Top Position on UK Midweek Chart; Elektra Artist Slated for October 9th Performance on Saturday Night Live; Dates Already Sold Out on First-Ever U.S. Headline Tour; \"Doo-Wops & Hooligans,\" Arrives October 5th|date=September 22, 2010|publisher=Marketwire|accessdate=October 1, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929011342/http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/Bruno-Mars-Soars-1-on-Billboard-Hot-100-Chart-With-Debut-Single-Just-The-Way-You-Are-1323732.htm|archivedate=September 29, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and lyrical interpretation==\n{{listen|filename=Bruno Mars - Just the Way You Are.ogg|title=\"Just the Way You Are\"\n|description=An 18-second sample of the song's [[refrain|chorus]]\n|pos= right\n|format=[[Ogg]]\n}}\n\"Just The Way You Are\" is a [[pop music|pop]], [[Rhythm and blues|R&B]] and [[soft rock]] ballad.<ref name=\"The Guardian\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/music/album-reviews/bruno-mars/|title=Bruno Mars: Now Magazine|last=Ritchie|first=Kevin|work=[[Now (newspaper)|Now Magazine]]|date=November 11, 2010|accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref> Its instrumentation features [[piano]] and a \"hip-hop [[breakbeat]]\".<ref name=\"just the way you are review of billboard\"/> Tim Byron of [[The Vine]] said \"the steeply rising melody at the start of the chorus introduces a little tension before defusing it with the, catchy tag of the chorus, which is simple and effective as a hook\".<ref name=\"The Vine\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thevine.com.au/music/single-reviews/number-ones-bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are-20101026-250915|title=Number Ones - Bruno Mars 'Just The Way You Are'|first=Tim|last=Byron|publisher=[[The Vine]]|date=October 26, 2010|accessdate=October 26, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007214323/http://www.thevine.com.au/music/single-reviews/number-ones-bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are-20101026-250915|archivedate=October 7, 2014 }}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' music reviewer, Paul Lester, describes the song as \"fairly standard R&B pop, his vocal a breezy falsetto as characterless.\"<ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2010/sep/13/new-band-bruno-mars|title=Bruno Mars (No 865)|first=Paul|last=Lester|work=The Guardian|date=September 13, 2010|accessdate=October 26, 2013}}</ref> The song is in the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[F major]] and has a sequence of F\u2013Dm\u2013B{{flat}}\u2013F. Mars' vocal range spans from [[F (musical note)|F<sub>3</sub>]] to [[C (musical note)|C<sub>5</sub>]].<ref name=\"musicnotes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0086091|title=Bruno Mars Just the Way You Are&nbsp;\u2013 Digital Sheet Music|publisher= Musicnotes.com. [[Alfred Music Publishing]]|accessdate=October 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' called \"Just The Way You Are\" \"a feel-good jam, in which Mars' is able to take \"to the next level\" is dreamy [[soprano]]\".<ref name=\"just the way you are review of billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1068877/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are|title=Bruno Mars, \"Just the Way You Are|work=Billboard|date=August 6, 2010|accessdate=October 25, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151122062652/http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1068877/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are|archivedate=November 22, 2015}}</ref> Leah Greenblatt  of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' labeled the song \"sweetly smitten ballad\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20430431,00.html|title=Bruno Mars&nbsp;\u2013 Doo-Woops & Holigans (2010)|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Leah|last=Greenblatt |date=September 29, 2010|accessdate=October 25, 2013}}</ref> Nick Levine from ''[[Digital Spy]]'' describe it as a \"huge-hearted urbany piano ballad with a similar instant classic feel to \"[[Empire State of Mind]]\".\"<ref name=\"Digital Spy Review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/review/a279472/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are.html|title=Bruno Mars: 'Just The Way You Are'|first=Nick|last=Levine|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=September 30, 2010|accessdate=October 25, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131208234622/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/review/a279472/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are.html|archivedate=December 8, 2013}}</ref> From The Guardian, Paul Lester says the lyrics are \"about a girl Mars could \"kiss all day\"\".<ref name=\"The Guardian\"/> The song has been compared to a \"[[U2]] production\" by Jon Caramanica of ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/06/arts/music/06mars.html|title=Bruno Mars in Ascension|date=October 5, 2010|first=Jon|last=Caramanica|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=October 5, 2010}}</ref> and by Andy Gill adding that he felt a \"groove through R&B territory\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Gill|first=Andy|date=January 14, 2011|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-bruno-mars-doowops-amp-hooligans-elektra-2183975.html|title=Album: Bruno Mars, Doo-Wops & Hooligans (Elektra)|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Tim Sendra of [[AllMusic]] called the debut single \"lushly romantic\".<ref name=\"AMTS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/doo-wops-hooligans-mw0002043948|title=Doo-Wops & Hooligans: Bruno Mars|first=Tim|last=Sendra|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=October 6, 2010}}</ref> Scott Kara for the ''[[New Zealand Herald]]'' felt the song was a \"ballad boogie\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/music/news/article.cfm?c_id=264&objectid=10690876|title=Album Review: Bruno Mars ''Doo-wops and Hooligans''|date=November 27, 2010|first=Scott|last=Kara|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=November 29, 2010}}</ref>\n \nLyrically, the song is about Mars professing \"his love for a beautiful girl who occupies his dreams\". ''Billboard'' carries on with its explanation \"Mars professes his love...\"When you smile, the whole world stops and stares for a while/ 'Cause girl you're amazing, just the way you are\". She concludes, \"Mars' lyrics aim to make female listeners feel nothing short of perfect in their own skin\".<ref name=\"just the way you are review of billboard\"/> Tim Byron of The Vine said the song is \"effective \u2013 the repeated lines at the start of the verses are catchy\".<ref name=\"The Vine\"/> ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''{{'}}s Alex Young described the song \"Mars sticks to the song\u2019s name and insists that he wouldn\u2019t want to change anything about his particular gal. You believe him, too. With an undeniably catchy chorus\".<ref name=\"CoSAY\">{{cite web|last=Young|first=Alex|date=December 3, 2010|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2010/12/album-review-bruno-mars-doo-wops-hooligans/|title=Album Review: Bruno Mars \u2013 Doo-Wops & Hooligans|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Reception and accolades==\nThe song has received mixed reviews from music critics. ''Digital Spy''{{'}}s Nick Levine gave the song four out of five stars and described it as a \"huge-hearted urbany piano ballad\" and compared its sound to \"Empire State of Mind\" by [[Alicia Keys]].<ref name=\"Digital Spy Review\"/> ''Billboard'' wrote: \"Mars professes his love for a beautiful girl who occupies his dreams [...] with its steady, danceable pulse and singalong chorus, Mars has created a feel-good jam that should establish him as a solo contender in his own right.\"<ref name=\"just the way you are review of billboard\"/> Alex Young from ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' praised the track's chorus for being \"undeniably catchy\" and didn't find surprising for the single to be a \"radio staple\".<ref name=\"CoSAY\"/> [[AllMusic]]'s Tim Sendra gave the single a mixed review saying, \"it\u2019s not very deep and it\u2019s not poetry, but sweetly played and sung\". He believes it, \"will melt hearts from tweens to old folk\".<ref name=\"AMTS\"/> Tim Byron of The Vine compared Mars' debut solo single to [[Billy Joel]]'s \"Just The Way You Are\", saying that the latter \"is a little more ambiguous...more aware of the ups and downs that characterize relationships\".<ref name=\"The Vine\"/> Jamie Milton of ''[[musicOMH]]'' explained that \"Just the Way You Are\" can be mistaken for a pop song due to its tempo. However, it is one of the most \"sappiestballad\" to be heard in a some time.<ref>{{cite web|last=Milton|first=Jamie|date=January 17, 2011|url=http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/bruno-mars-doo-wops-and-hooligans|title=Bruno Mars \u2013 Doo-Wops And Hooligans|work=[[musicOMH]]|accessdate=February 11, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116162852/http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/bruno-mars-doo-wops-and-hooligans|archivedate=January 16, 2017}}</ref> Nima Baniamer from [[Contactmusic.com]] felt the single didn't make Mars stand out from other R&B artists. Baniamer added, \"The song never builds to any climax and it simply falls a bit flat, coming across quite corny and cheesy.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Baniamer|first=Nima|title=Bruno Mars - Just The Way You Are Single Review|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/single-review/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are|magazine=[[Contactmusic.com]]|accessdate=October 3, 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe song was nominated for the 2010 [[The Record of the Year]] ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roty.tv/|publisher=Roty.TV|accessdate=July 30, 2015|title=The Winner is...|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111002130347/http://www.roty.tv/|archivedate=October 2, 2011}}</ref> In 2011, the song won the [[Grammy Award]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Male Pop Vocal Performance|Best Male Pop Vocal Performance]]. The single was nominated for several awards at [[2011 Billboard Music Awards]] such as [[Billboard Music Award for Top Hot 100 Song|Top Hot 100 Song]] and Top Pop Song, but it ended up by winning only the category [[Billboard Music Award for Top Radio Song|Top Radio Song]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/471886/2011-billboard-music-awards-winners-list|title=2011 Billboard Music Awards Winners List|work=Billboard|date=April 25, 2011|accessdate=November 4, 2018}}</ref> It was nominated for [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music \u2013 Love Song|Choice Music: Love Song]] at the [[2011 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/06/29/teen-choice-awards-2011-nominees_n_887197.html|title=Teen Choice Awards 2011 Nominees Announced: Harry Potter vs Twilight|work=The Huffington Post|date=June 29, 2011|accessdate=May 28, 2014}}</ref> In the same year, the single won Most Performed Song at ASCAP Pop Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2011/most_Performed_Songs.aspx|title=ASCAP Awards 2011 \u2013 Most Performed Songs|publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]]|date=27 April 2011|accessdate=28 April 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110501130724/http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2011/most_Performed_Songs.aspx|archivedate=1 May 2011}}</ref> In 2012, at the same award ceremony, it won, again, Most Performed Song and also Song of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2012/most_Performed_Songs.aspx|title=ASCAP Awards 2012 \u2013 Most Performed Songs|publisher=American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|date=18 April 2012|accessdate=19 April 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423024619/https://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2012/most_Performed_Songs.aspx|archivedate=23 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2012/songofyear.aspx|title=ASCAP Awards 2012 \u2013 Song of the Year|publisher=American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|date=April 18, 2012|accessdate=May 30, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829021058/http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/popawards/2012/songofyear.aspx|archivedate=August 29, 2016}}</ref> At the [[RTHK]] International Pop Poll Awards the song won \"Top 10 Gold International Gold Songs\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rthk.hk/special/poppoll22/|title=22nd International Pop Poll|work=[[RTHK]]|date=May 2, 2012|accessdate=January 4, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513044650/http://rthk.hk/special/poppoll22/|archivedate=May 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song reached the top of the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 on the chart dated October 2, 2010, ending the two-week reign of [[Katy Perry]]'s \"[[Teenage Dream (Katy Perry song)|Teenage Dream]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/956176/bruno-mars-lands-atop-hot-100-rihanna-roars-into-top-10|title=Bruno Mars Lands Atop Hot 100, Rihanna Roars Into Top 10|first=Silvio|last=Pietroluongo|date=September 22, 2010|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=September 22, 2010}}</ref> The song spent a total of 48 weeks on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, debuting on August 7, 2010 and leaving the chart on July 2, 2011. As of October 2015, the song had sold 6.7 million downloads domestically.<ref name=us_sales>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6715365/ask-billboard-lady-gaga-first-artist-with-two-7-million-selling |title=Ask Billboard: Lady Gaga First Artist With Two 7-Million-Selling Downloads |last=Trust |first=Gary |work=Billboard|date=October 2, 2015 |accessdate=October 3, 2015}}</ref> The song was certified diamond by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA).<ref name=\"RIAA\"/> It holds the record of the longest-reigning debut format on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]], having spent 20 weeks atop.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/428841/top-50-music-stars-of-the-50-states/12|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Born in the U.S.A.: Top 50 Stars of the 50 States|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 4, 2013|date=July 3, 2013}}</ref> It first featured on the Greatest of All Time Hot 100 at number 79.<ref name=\"GAT\"/> The song peaked at number one on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] and was certified six times platinum by [[Music Canada]] (MC).<ref name=\"CAN\"/><ref name=\"MC\"/>\n\nOn September 26, 2010, it became the singer's second number-one single in the United Kingdom,<ref name=\"sc_UK_Bruno Mars\" /> where it hit the number-one spot again on October 24, 2010 <ref name=\"KOL\"/> from sales of 116,000 copies<ref name=\"KOL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/record-breaking-kings-of-leon-reign-again-biggest-first-week-album-of-year-so-far-biggest-first-week-digital-album-of-all-time/ |title=Record Breaking Kings Of Leon Reign Again *biggest first week album of|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=October 24, 2010|accessdate=October 24, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110217101806/http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/record-breaking-kings-of-leon-reign-again-biggest-first-week-album-of-year-so-far-biggest-first-week-digital-album-of-all-time/|archivedate=February 17, 2011}}</ref> becoming the first song ever to have left the top three before rebounding to the top spot. It sold 766,000 copies during 2010, becoming the third biggest seller of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/cardle-at-no-1-again-eminemrihanna-take-that-scoop-2010-crowns/|title=Cardle at No 1 again - Eminem/Rihanna & Take That scoop 2010 crowns|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=January 2, 2011|accessdate=2011-11-03|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110107094350/http://www.theofficialcharts.com/chart-news/cardle-at-no-1-again-eminemrihanna-take-that-scoop-2010-crowns/|archivedate=January 7, 2011}}</ref> On April 9, 2013 it was revealed that the song is the ninth most downloaded song of all time in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1075914/uk-digital-single-downloads-hit-one-billion|title=Top 10 UK Downloads Of All-Time|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=April 9, 2013|accessdate=December 17, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130412230823/http://news.sky.com/story/1075914/uk-digital-single-downloads-hit-one-billion|archivedate=April 12, 2013}}</ref> On 2 August 2011 \"Just The Way You Are\" became the 108th million-selling single in the UK, having taken 43 weeks to reach that figure.<ref name=\"MWJul2011\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.musicweek.com/index.php/news/read/adele-makes-uk-digital-first/046145|date=5 July 2011|first=Ben|last=Cardew|title=Adele makes UK digital first|journal=[[Music Week]]|accessdate=September 8, 2012}}</ref> As of September 2017, in the United Kingdom, the single had reached a total of 1,57 million combined sales (1.33 million purchases and 244,72 streaming equivalent sales), becoming the 75th biggest selling single of all-time in UK. \"Just the Way You Are\" is the seventeenth [[List of best-selling singles of the 21st century in the United Kingdom#Best-selling singles based on paid-for sales|best-selling single based on paid-for sales of the 21st century in the United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-uks-official-chart-millionaires-revealed__20459/|title=The UK's Official Chart 'millionaires' revealed|first=Rob|last=Copsey|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=September 19, 2017}}</ref> It was certified three times platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI).<ref name=\"UKCert\"/> On October 12, 2010, Bruno Mars got his third number one single in the [[Dutch Top 40]], after \"[[Nothin' On You]]\" and \"[[Billionaire (Travie McCoy song)|Billionaire]]\", having spent 11 weeks at number one in Netherlands.<ref name=NET/> The song also reached number one in Australia and certified seven times platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA).<ref name=\"ARIAS\"/><ref name=\"ARIAC\"/> The single debuted at number 31 in New Zealand on August 2, 2010. The song was number 1 for two weeks. The single was on the chart for 32 weeks.<ref name=\"NZ\"/>\n\n\"Just the Way You Are\" was less successful on the [[French Singles Chart]], where it peaked at number 33 and stayed on the chart for 28 weeks.<ref name=\"Fra\"/> \"Just The Way You Are\" also peaked at number three in Switzerland,<ref name=\"SWI\"/> at number one in the Republic of Ireland,<ref name=\"IRE\"/> at number four in Belgium (Flanders),<ref name=\"FLA\"/> and at number 2 in Germany and Sweden.<ref name=\"GER\"/><ref name=\"SWE\"/> It reached number six at Denmark.<ref name=\"DEN\"/> \"Just the Way You Are\" was the [[List of best-selling singles|best selling digital single]] of 2011, selling more than 12.5 million copies globally throughout that year, thus becoming one of the [[list of best-selling singles worldwide|best-selling singles of all time]].<ref name=\"IFPI\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.ifpi.org/content/library/DMR2012.pdf|title=IFPI Digital Music Report 2012: The global top-selling digital singles of 2011|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|format=PDF|page=7|accessdate=January 1, 2015}}</ref> The song is also one of the [[Official Charts Company|UK]]'s biggest selling singles of all-time placed at number 74 with sales around 1.17 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/daft-punks-get-lucky-becomes-one-of-the-uks-biggest-selling-singles-of-all-time-2315/|title=Daft Punk\u2019s Get Lucky becomes one of the UK\u2019s biggest selling singles of all-time!|first=Daniel|last=Lane|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=June 27, 2013|accessdate=October 1, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701050851/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/daft-punks-get-lucky-becomes-one-of-the-uks-biggest-selling-singles-of-all-time-2315/|archivedate=July 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n\n===Development and synopsis===\n[[File:Bruno Mars - Just the way you are video.jpg|thumb|left|Bruno Mars arranging himself in a cassette tape in the shape of him playing the piano, in the music video.]]\nThe corresponding music video was directed by Ethan Lander, shot in September 2010 in the downtown of [[Los Angeles]] and released on September 8, 2010.<ref name=\"JTWYA behind the scenes\"/><ref name=\"Marketwire\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2010/09/08/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are-video/|title=Bruno Mars wows his lady with cassette tape drawings in 'Just the Way You Are' video: Watch here|date=September 8, 2010|first=Brad|last=Wete|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=September 8, 2010}}</ref> Cameron Duddy was able to shoot the behind-the-scenes footage in exchange for his jean jacket, which Mars used during the music video.<ref name=\"NYPHP\">{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2017/08/25/this-guy-once-lent-bruno-mars-a-jacket-now-theyre-a-creative-dream-team/|title=This guy once lent Bruno Mars a jacket; now, they\u2019re a creative dream team|last=Phull|first=Hardeep|work=[[New York Post]]|date=August 25, 2017|accessdate=October 13, 2017}}</ref> The video features Peruvian-Australian actress [[Nathalie Kelley]]. Lander considers Bruno Mars a star. He adds \"The charisma that he has, you can\u2019t teach.\" Finishing with \"singer even manages to be suave in his mugshot, which is no small feat!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/5642412/bruno-mars-just-the-way-you-are-behind-the-scenes|title=Go Behind The Scenes Of Bruno Mars\u2019 \"Just The Way You Are\"|first=Becky|last=Bain|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=September 30, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2013}}</ref> He sees the video as a collaboration, the video director came up with the vision and Mars added his vision and so on. The video is a mixture of live action and stopped animation and through the animation, Bruno shows his girlfriend how beautiful she is. He takes a cassette tape and starts creating images out of the tape and they start to get a life of their own.<ref name=\"JTWYA behind the scenes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r-s8R6jQjdc|title=Bruno Mars - The Making Of 'Just The Way You Are'|publisher=Youtube.com|date=September 29, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe video begins with Kelley listening to \"Just the Way You Are\" on her [[Walkman]] as Mars walks in. Mars stops the tape player, removes the cassette tape and begins singing his song.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/956429/bruno-mars-is-love-struck-in-just-the-way-you-are-clip|title=Bruno Mars Is Love-Struck In 'Just The Way You Are' Clip|first=Mariel|last=Concepcion|work=Billboard|publisher=|date=September 8, 2010|accessdate=October 25, 2013}}</ref> As the instrumental portion of the song begins, Mars pulls the media out of the cassette tape and arranges the media into letters forming his name followed by the song title. As the song continues, he forms a picture of a drum, again on the table, using the tape media. Additional images of similar construction follow throughout the video including a portrait of Mars as well as one of Kelley blinking her eyes and smiling as Mars continues singing. Most of the images shown are animated, including a bell which Mars rings with his fingers in synchronization with the [[chimes]] near the end of the song. Lastly, Mars finishes the song while singing and playing an [[upright piano]] while Kelley watches and smiles. The video was inspired by the artwork of Erika Iris Simmons.<ref name=\"Soars\"/>\n\n===Reception===\nIt has received strong airplay on [[VH1 Europe]], reaching number one on the VH1 Pop Chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/vh1s-top-20-countdown/november-6-2010-1362656/|title=VH1's Top 20 Countdown Season 9 Episode 45|publisher=tv.com|date=November 6, 2010|accessdate=October 7, 2013}}</ref> At the [[2011 MTV Video Music Aid Japan]] the music video won [[MTV Video Music Award Japan for Best Male Video|Best Male Video]].<ref>{{cite news|last= |first=|date=|url=http://www.mtvjapan.com/news/music/19340/|title=\u300cMTV Video Music Aid Japan\u300d\u8996\u8074\u8005\u6295\u7968\u306b\u3088\u308b\u53d7\u8cde\u4f5c\u54c1\u3092\u767a\u8868|language=Japanese|work=MTV Japan|accessdate=July 2, 2011}}</ref> In 2011, the video won [[Myx Music Award for Favorite International Video|Favorite International Video]] at the [[MYX Music Awards]] and received three nominations at the [[2011 MuchMusic Video Awards|MuchMusic Video Awards]], [[MuchMusic Video Award for Best International Artist Video|International Video of the Year - Artist]], Most Watched Video of the Year and [[MuchMusic Video Award for Peoples Choice: Favourite International Video|UR Fave International Video]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/03/16/11/yeng-dominates-myx-music-awards-2011|title=Yeng dominates myx music awards 2011|last=Santos|first=Nikki delos|work=[[ABS-CBN]]|date=March 16, 2011|accessdate=July 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222030115/http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/03/16/11/yeng-dominates-myx-music-awards-2011|archive-date=December 22, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/justin-bieber-lady-gaga-britney-189171|title=Justin Bieber, Lady Gaga and Britney Spears Grab Canadian Music Video Award Nominations|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 17, 2011|accessdate=July 6, 2011}}</ref> It received the award for Popular International Music Video at the Channel [V] Thailand Music Video Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.student-weekly.com/260911/entertain6.html|title=Channel V day|last=Chaiyong|first=Suwitcha|work=Student-Weekly|accessdate=December 7, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001083407/http://www.student-weekly.com/260911/entertain6.html |archivedate=October 1, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> As of November 2019, the music video has received over 1.4 billion views on [[YouTube]].\n\n==Live performances==\nBruno Mars performed the song at the [[Bowery Ballroom]] in [[New York City]] on August&nbsp;25, 2010, with him and his four-piece band dressed in blue tuxedos and black skinny ties. John Macdonald for ''Spin'' said \"Despite a couple pitch problems here and there, Mars proved to be nearly as good a performer as he is a songwriter\".<ref name=\"Spin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2010/08/hitmaker-bruno-mars-wows-ladies-ny-debut/|title=Hitmaker Bruno Mars Wows the Ladies in NY Debut|first=John S. W.|last=MacDonald|date=August 26, 2010|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|accessdate=September 9, 2010}}</ref> Mars performed the song on ''[[SNL|Saturday Night Live]]'' on October 9, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/viral-videos/954357/bruno-mars-performs-just-the-way-you-are-on-snl|title=Bruno Mars Performs 'Just The Way You Are' on 'SNL'|first=Walter|last=Frazier|work=Billboard|date=October 11, 2010|accessdate=December 16, 2013}}</ref> The song was performed at ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', on October 14, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/5656531/bruno-mars-serenades-ellen-degeneres-with-just-the-way-you-are|title=Bruno Mars Serenades Ellen DeGeneres With \"Just The Way You Are\"|first=Becky|last=Bain|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=October 14, 2010 |accessdate=December 16, 2012}}</ref> A soulful arrangement of the song was sung for a ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Tastemakers video session, on October 22, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/953194/bruno-mars-live-billboard-tastemakers-video|title=Bruno Mars Live: Billboard Tastemakers|first=Lisa|last=Binkert|work=Billboard|date=October 21, 2010|accessdate=November 15, 2010}}</ref> An acoustic version of the song was performed at ''Grammy Nominations'' concert in 2010 for the [[53rd Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/katy-perry-bruno-mars-justin-bieber-hit-the-stage-at-grammy-nominations-concert|title=Katy Perry, Bruno Mars, Justin Bieber Hit the Stage at Grammy Nominations Concert|first=Joyce|last=Lee|publisher=[[CBS]]|date=February 4, 2011|accessdate=December 16, 2013}}</ref> Mars also played the song live at the [[BBC Radio 1Xtra]] [[Live Lounge]] and at the ''[[2011 NBA All-Star Game|NBA All-Star Tip Off Pre-Show]]'' in January and February 2011, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/5774591/bruno-mars-and-keri-hilson-nba-all-star-show?|title=Bruno Mars And Keri Hilson Score At NBA All Star Pre-Game Show|last=Daw|first=Robbie|publisher=Idolator|date=February 21, 2011|accessdate=November 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/sessions/2011-01-19_brunomars|title=It's Bruno Mars' first time in the Live Lounge|publisher=[[BBC Radio]]|date=January 19, 2011|accessdate=December 29, 2019}}</ref> The song was also performed on ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|NBC's Today Show]]'' on June 24, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1666382/bruno-mars-today-show-performance.jhtml|title=Bruno Mars Fans Brave Rain For 'Today' Performance|last=Genet|first=Danielle|work=[[MTV News]]|date=June 24, 2011|accessdate=March 1, 2014}}</ref> A live performance was also done on the French ''[[X Factor (French TV series)|X Factor]]'' during the finale of the second season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13956826|title=Briton Matthew Raymond-Barker wins French X Factor|author=BBC staff|work=[[BBC News]]|date=29 June 2011|accessdate=December 16, 2013}}</ref> Carolina Frost for the [[Huffington Post]] said that Mars at the [[2012 Brit Awards]] \"took his poptastic song Just the Way You Are, and gave it a fresh jazzy arrangement.\" While Tweeter David Quantick summed up his opinion, asking if \"someone came as a spare Osmond\". Others praised Mars' vocality and confidence with his soulful rendition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2012/02/21/brit-awards-2012-performe_n_1292271.html|title=Brit Awards 2012: Performances Review: Adele, Coldplay, Blur, Ed Sheeran, Rihanna, Bruno Mars, Noel Gallagher|first=Carolina|last=Frost|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=February 21, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2013}}</ref> It was the twelfth song of his debut worldwide tour, [[The Doo-Wops & Hooligans Tour]] (2010\u201312)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/music/bruno-mars-at-martini-ranch-last-night-video-6619969|title=Bruno Mars at Martini Ranch Last Night (Video)|date=November 21, 2010|first=Nicki|last=Escudero|work=[[Phoenix New Times]]\n|accessdate=November 22, 2010}}</ref> and was fourteenth on the set list of his second worldwide tour, [[The Moonshine Jungle Tour]] (2013\u201314).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/bruno-mars-sprinkles-his-solid-594654|title=Bruno Mars Sprinkles Solid Gold Dust at L.A. Tour Stop (And We Love It): Concert Review|first=Shirley|last=Halperin|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=July 28, 2013|accessdate=October 25, 2013}}</ref> The single was performed as the last song in his set list for his performance at [[Super Bowl XLVIII halftime show]] as a Tribute to the [[United States Armed Forces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/super-bowl-2014/5893849/watch-bruno-mars-super-bowl-halftime-performance|title=Bruno Mars Gets One-Sided Super Bowl Bouncing With Biggest Hits|first=Kevin|last=Rutherford|work=Billboard|date=February 2, 2014|accessdate=February 8, 2014}}</ref> In 2017, the singer participated in the \"Somos Una Voz\" relief initiative concert by singing a Spanish version of \"Just the Way You Are\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/bruno-mars-performs-just-way-you-are-spanish|title=Bruno Mars Performs \"Just The Way You Are\" in Spanish and It Will Give You Goosebumps|last=Meija|first=Maxiel|work=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]|date=October 16, 2017|accessdate=August 19, 2018}}</ref> On his third worldwide tour, the [[24K Magic World Tour]] (2017\u201318), the track was the fourteenth or fifteenth track of the setlist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://los40.com/los40/2017/04/04/los40trending/1491290107_039226.html|title=Bruno Mars pase\u00f3 por Madrid su candidatura al trono del pop|last=Paniagua|first=Arturo|work=PRISA|language=Spanish|date=April 4, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blitz.sapo.pt/principal/update/2017-04-05-Ele-e-funk-ele-e-rock-ele-e-um-romantico.-Bruno-Mars-fe-la-bonita-em-Lisboa|title=Ele \u00e9 funk, ele \u00e9 rock, ele \u00e9 um rom\u00e2ntico. Bruno Mars f\u00ea-la bonita em Lisboa|last=Guerra|first=Lu\u00eds|work=[[Blitz (magazine)|Blitz]]|language=Portuguese|date=April 5, 2017|accessdate=April 18, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170408083206/http://blitz.sapo.pt/principal/update/2017-04-05-Ele-e-funk-ele-e-rock-ele-e-um-romantico.-Bruno-Mars-fe-la-bonita-em-Lisboa|archive-date=April 8, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Cover versions and usage on other media==\n\"Just the Way You Are\" has been covered several times. It was first covered by [[Nathan Sykes]] from [[The Wanted]], [[The Saturdays]] at [[BBC Radio 1]]'s ''[[Live Lounge]]'' on October 29, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/events/er38q9|title=Live Lounge from The Saturdays|publisher=BBC Radio 1|date=October 29, 2010|accessdate=July 11, 2019}}</ref> San Diego-based formed band, [[Pierce the Veil]] covered the track for the [[compilation album]] ''[[Punk Goes Pop 4]]'', which was released on November 21, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/6046852/bruno-mars-pierce-the-veil-punk-goes-pop-vol-4-premiere |title=Bruno Mars' \"Just The Way You Are\" Gets Covered By Pierce The Veil: Idolator Premiere|last=Bain|first=Becky|publisher=Idolator|date=September 17, 2011|accessdate=November 3, 2011}}</ref> It was performed by [[Cory Monteith]] on \"[[Furt]]\", an episode of the American TV show ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' which aired on November 23, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/5695491/glee-bruno-mars|title=\u2018Glee\u2019 Has Got Bruno Mars Covered \u2014 Listen To \"Just The Way You Are\" And \"Marry You\"|first=Becky|last=Bain|publisher=Idolator|date=November 19, 2010|accessdate=December 17, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Semigran |first=Aly |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1652987/bruno-mars-just-way-gets-glee-treatment.jhtml |title=Bruno Mars' 'Just The Way You Are' Gets The 'Glee' Treatment |work=MTV News |date=November 24, 2010 |accessdate=January 26, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106111954/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1652987/bruno-mars-just-way-gets-glee-treatment.jhtml |archivedate=November 6, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The show's cover version achieved moderate success by peaking at number 24 in Canada.<ref name=\"GleeCan100\"/> It reached number 40 in the United States, 47 in Australia and number 48 in Ireland.<ref name=\"Hot 100Glee\"/><ref name=\"AusGlee\"/><ref name=\"IreGlee\"/>\n\n[[Daniel Evans (singer)|Daniel Evans]], a finalist on [[The X Factor (UK)]], included his version of the song on his album ''Wicked Game'', released on December 2, 2013. The album contains covers from various artists.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wicked-game/id1042350586|title=iTunes - Wicked Game by Daniel Evans|publisher=iTunes Store|date=December 2, 2013|accessdate=March 26, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326230449/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wicked-game/id1042350586|archivedate=March 26, 2016}}</ref> [[Matt Cardle]], the winner of [[The X Factor (UK series 7)|the seventh series]] of British TV talent contest ''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]'', performed \"Just the Way You Are\" in week 2 of the live shows and later recorded his own version of the song as a [[B-side]] for his debut single \"[[Many of Horror#When We Collide|When We Collide]]\".\n\nIn 2012, Dominican musician [[Karlos Ros\u00e9]] covered the song in [[bachata (music)|bachata]] as his debut single which peaked at number 31 on the [[Hot Latin Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs]] chart and number one on the [[Tropical Songs|''Billboard'' Tropical Songs]] chart in the United States.<ref name=\"KRLS\"/><ref name=\"KRTA\"/> The music video for his cover was filmed in New York City and directed by Robert Kruz.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tr3s.com/music/artists/k-rose/|title=K. Rose|language=Spanish|work=[[MTV Tres]]|accessdate=January 27, 2014}}</ref> The original version is featured in the movie ''[[Pitch Perfect]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundtrack.net/movie/think-like-a-man/|title=Pitch Perfect - Song Credits|work=[[Soundtrack.Net]]|date=April 20, 2012|accessdate=June 20, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328154905/http://www.soundtrack.net/movie/pitch-perfect/|archivedate=March 28, 2016}}</ref> American singer [[Johnny Mathis]] covered the song in his album, ''[[Johnny Mathis Sings the Great New American Songbook]]'' (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/johnny-mathis-sings-the-great-new-american-songbook-mw0003108825|title= Johnny Mathis Sings the Great New American Songbook \u2013 Johnny Mathis|website=AllMusic|accessdate=November 25, 2017}}</ref> [[Dana International]] performed the song during the interval of the first semi-final of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2019]] in Tel Aviv.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/cultura/interior/conan-osiris-fora-da-final-da-eurovisao-10898402.html|title=Conan Os\u00edris fora da final da Eurovis\u00e3o|language=Portuguese|last=Ferreira|first=Ana Bela|work=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|date=May 14, 2019|accessdate=May 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* '''Digital download'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/just-the-way-you-are-single/id382513480 |title=iTunes - Music - Just the Way You Are - Single by Bruno Mars |publisher=iTunes|date=July 20, 2010 |accessdate=September 22, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100727003805/http://itunes.apple.com/us/album/just-the-way-you-are-single/id382513480 |archivedate=July 27, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n# \"Just the Way You Are\" (Album Version)&nbsp;\u2013 3:40\n\n* '''Digital download&nbsp